<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">treestout</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Ok, now that i have 2 ssoys, i find that i'm often out of stamina when meleeing 2 or more 40+ mobs down.  I was always under the impression that your attack speed went down when you run out of stamina, but in another post, several people thought otherwise.  Does anybody have proof that no stamina affects damage/atk speed at all?  This will have implications for all dual wielding melee types who don't have massive stamina like ogres.  It'll also affect stamina draining zones such as kedge.<P>------------------<BR>"First you cleave the knee, then you cleave the head."<P>Meyer Anklebane,<BR>on taking down Hill Giants<BR>41 Halfling Warrior, Xegony<P>"I am NOT a smurf!  There are no smurfs in Everquest!"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Raggrok Skullcrusha</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Yeah, it would be nice if someone could parse it, but I notice to obvious effect at "no stamina" in kedge when I fight there.  Could be because I am an ogre and I am never really "out of stamina" for very long, but I doubt it...<P>If there is an effect, it's minimal.<P>------------------<BR>-Raggrok Skullcrusha<P>50th Ogre Warrior; RZ</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Immudan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Well I haven't done any parsing to test it but it seems like I'm swinging slower with no stamina.  Usually isn't an issue unless I'm fighting in Kedge or using my Fleshripper (damn that thing's heavy).<P>------------------<BR>Khumak - 42 Ogre Warrior<BR>Hasima - 8 Dark Elf Necro<BR>Immudan - 11 Erudite Wizard<BR>(Rodcet Nife)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Jumamdar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Im dual wielding Brazen Brass Kilij's which are pretty  heavy at a weight of 8.5 each. My stamina is 110. In long fights, my stamina drops VERY low but never goes below zero. SO I never see a difference. I do know, however, that if it DOES go below zero then you will lose agility. The only time I drop below zero is when I start jumping while running. <P>Sorry no parse logs. But I wouldnt worry too much about stamina. Next time your fighting just check out your stats to see if any are red. <P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kutulu Valkyriur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">It was my impression that it only affected your speed if your health was at the  critical rate (when AGI starts fallin etc) and when you are encoumbered. Other then that I dont know.<P>------------------<BR>--Kutulu Valkyriur,<BR>     Monk and Leader of the Downward Spiral<BR>--Zaman Kuthuleth, <BR>Troll Shaman of the Downward Spiral</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Immudan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Well in Kedge Keep just the fact that you are in water drains your stamina.  My stamina is 157 and by the end of each fight my stamina bar is empty.  The best way I know of to avoid this is to get an augmentation buff.  I never realized how many things get buffed by that til I read the spell description.  Not as much of a speed boost as some of the others, but when you combine a speed boost with a agi boost and a stamina regen boost...<P>------------------<BR>Khumak - 42 Ogre Warrior<BR>Hasima - 8 Dark Elf Necro<BR>Immudan - 11 Erudite Wizard<BR>(Rodcet Nife)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Noreal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">With my wizard in Kedge, when I drop down below around 1/3 a bubble of stamina, my strength begins to drop, dexterity falls, and agility as well.<P>With my warrior, I haven't noticed such detrimental affects to being out of stamina, and I don't seem to swing noticably slower..</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
